Title:
Payment form fails to process valid credit card (Stripe integration)

Description:
When a user fills out the payment form with a valid credit card and submits it, the form returns a generic error and the payment is not processed.

Steps to Reproduce:

Go to https://example.com/checkout

Fill in all required billing fields

Enter a valid credit card number (e.g. test Visa 4242 4242 4242 4242)

Click the "Pay Now" button

Expected Result:
Payment should be processed successfully, and the user should be redirected to the confirmation page.

Actual Result:
An error message appears: "Something went wrong. Please try again."
